  "articleSummary": "The article argues that \"generative UI\" is not a single technology but a layered problem, and it provides a map to navigate the ecosystem. It identifies four distinct layers—product shell, UI composition model, runtime/transport, and agent/tool backend—and warns against conflating them. The piece also introduces a control spectrum from tool-to-component rendering to declarative catalogs to iframe mini-apps, emphasizing the trade-off between developer control and agent freedom. Written in an analytical, explanatory tone for developers and architects building LLM-powered interfaces, it uses metaphors like \"training wheels\" for chat and \"soup\" for blurred architectures to clarify the landscape.",
